letter from gma!! my moms dying--thats why i was cryin all day friday

Dear Soraya,
It's been a terrible week! No worse tha you have had... Jayne and Michael  Taylor appeared at my door last Thursday Morning __ and I was stunned. She looked terrible! Bruised, tired, sick,  drunk?  I couldn't tell...  they said they had driven all night, and were exhausted. I let them in ,telling them the house rules ___No smoking inside the house and no alcohol inside or out!
They agreed and came in. BIG MISTAKE.
The next day they seemed rested and OK?....and went out for sightseeing, interviewing for jobs....
In the meantime I was preoccupied with my own problems. Getting ready for surgery on Wednesday, shopping for soft food stuff, for soups,cathcing up on laundry, bills, doctor check, meds, getting subs for my church activities....getting Sheila lined up to take me to Knoxville for the surgery...
Anyway, I paid little attention to them as they came and went.
After my surgery Wednesday, Sheila brought me home and I told her that she could leave and Jayne would take care of me.  Little did I know.... I crashed. In pain and groggy from meds, I slept most of the time, but when I did come to occassionaly I thought Jayne was acting strangly...Mike was making soup....
It wasn't until Thursday afternoon that I really caught on. Jayne was drinking again, had fallen down and broken her tail bone __again.
I called Susan for Help __and got the whole family. We had an intervention. with their support, I gave Jayne her choices __Go to rehab or get out.  When she refused, We called the police. four came!  They FINALLY convinced her to go to the hospital. She did go, but would not go to rehab, so I locked my door, and wouldn't let them back in.
They left Friday morning. I am so sorry. I love her, but since she would not  go to rehab,  I cannot help her.  She must help herself.
I know she must be back in Florida. And I know she loves you and Mariah. But I don't know how much longer she can keep on doing what she's doing.  Destroying herself.  But from now on she must do it without me...
Thinking of you and hoping you are strong enough to bear all this....I love you. Hang in ...Think Ireland...and stay with that wonderful guy, that I've been hearing all about....Ryan, right? Hug your sister for me.
Love and prayers,
Nona

my mom got released yesterday...=[........&& today she called && left a message on our house phone (she doesnt know i have a cell) && anyways her message..."i love you mariah, i love my girls  (surprised to hear that...) im leaving for colorado....bye." i heard this message && i cried not because shes leaving, ohh no i doubt shes leaving, but the worst part about that message was....she was drunk. full on sluring her words....i hate her. && if she wants to go kill herself fine by me, drink til you have no more breaths leftl; see if i cry at your funeral....i will cry, but it wont be for you, it will be for my little sister, never having a good mother, i will cry for your brothers, && sisters, the ones that dropped EVERYTHING they were doing && drove/flew to florida the day they found out that u were in a treatment center!! i've done everything i could have possibley done to help her....fuck her....what a wonderful mother she was.

saturday...not very good...but got better---

my grandfather is visiting (leaving tomarrow =[) anyways...woke up..8:34am. dads out in lakewood ranch running && biking...so mariah, grandpa, && i are all just chillin @ the house...9am...door knocks...mariah answers, its my mother!! ahhgg she walks back to her friends car to get her backpack... i see that shes really drunk...she was swaying all over the sidewalk almost fell in the grass but grabbed the car just in time...i ran into my room && called my dad...he didnt answer, i sent him an "urgent" text message....he called 20minutes later...&& by then i was shaking out of control...my mom && sister were in the kitchen...i walked in there...my mom was sitting in the middle of the kitchen on the floor eating pizza...i heard my cell ringing, so i ran && answered it, it was dad!! yay i was saved...or not, i was crying so much he couldnt understand me, he was an hour away from his car, && the car was an hour away from the house...so he was two hours away...=[....he talked to my mom && told her to leave...she tried to stand up to hang up the phone, && fell flat on her face...i called the police, she wouldnt leave...i had to, she looked @ me && said please dont...i gave her a chance to leave, she wouldnt soo i called...i took my sister, locked her in my dads room, she watched cartoons, i went in my dads office got the court documents...my mom tried to take them from me, failed, && then tried to slap me, but almost fell, a male police officer came, he asked me lots of questions, && talked to my mom, he asked her, how she got there, she told him that a friend brought her, which WAS true, then a second cop arrived, he talked to me && then my mom, he also asked her how she got to the house, she replied "i walked", the first cop said i thought, some one dropped you off && she said, well he drove me half way && then i walked...i said, NO, she got dropped off right infront of the house....she looked @ me && said "fuck you, soraya, your not my daughter, my daughters not a bitch" the cops both yelled @ her...anyways they called my dad, talked to him, && then they made her leave, still yelling @ me, && they let her walk away from our house...well an hour later the police officer called me && told me, that they had let my mom walk down the street, but she was so drunk that, instead they took her to Manatee Glens, she has to stay there for 72hrs (3days)...&& if she goes crazy w/o having any alcoholic beverage...then she will have to stay longer!! yay!! im soo happy!! this means if she goes crazy, then she'll get help!! yay i hope soo!! then i went to eat, && then i went to the movies w/ RYAN!! yay
